{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/5-4. Virtual memory Part 2/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"minjun.blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"48c9d70b-b167-526a-b18a-1be9531b9e15","excerpt":"contents: 0-1. CA Intro Integrating TLB, Cache, Memory Aliasing in virtually addressed cache The same virtual address of different processes can be mapped to different physical address Wrong cache hi…","html":"<p>contents: <a href=\"/0-1.%20CA%20Intro\" data-wiki-link=\"true\">0-1. CA Intro</a></p>\n<h2>Integrating TLB, Cache, Memory</h2>\n<h3>Aliasing in virtually addressed cache</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>The same virtual address of different processes can be mapped to different physical address</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wrong cache hit can occur</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Different virtual addresses of different process can be mapped to the same physical address <br>(when some memory space is shared by multiple processes)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The physical memory can be cached in two different locations</li>\n<li>Coherency problem can happen <br>One program writes the data without the other program being aware that the data had changed</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h4>Simple solution</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Flush cache at context switching -> too high miss rate\n<ul>\n<li>Context switch: In multi-process environments, multiple processes share a single CPU</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h2>Hybrid cache: virtually-indexed  &#x26; physically-tagged cache</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>No aliasing problem</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>TLB &#x26; cache are accessed in a parallel manner (fast)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class='gatsby-resp-image-figure' style='margin-bottom: 16px;'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-wrapper' style='position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; '>\n      <a class='gatsby-resp-image-link' href='/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/62aaf/01%2013.jpg' style='display: block' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-background-image' style=\"padding-bottom: 42.94117647058824%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class='gatsby-resp-image-image' alt='01 13.jpg' title='' src='/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/a22ce/01%2013.jpg' srcset='/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/0b705/01%2013.jpg 170w,\n/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/31389/01%2013.jpg 340w,\n/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/a22ce/01%2013.jpg 680w,\n/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/29373/01%2013.jpg 1020w,\n/static/bcce4acb800619fea94a84273ae37a2f/62aaf/01%2013.jpg 1280w' sizes='(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px' style='width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;' loading='lazy' decoding='async'>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class='gatsby-resp-image-figcaption'>01 13.jpg</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<br></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>32-bit virtual address</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Page size = <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>p</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2^p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> Bytes</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Physical memory size =  <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2^t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7936em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7936em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> Bytes (t-bit physical address)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Block size = <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2^m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">m</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> words</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Num of sets in a cache = <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></msup></mrow><annotation 